title: Le Bistro Irlandais
description: "Frirlandais" food anyone?  The American chef Spencer Shidner doesn't mind too much what you call it - how could he since he often has kangaroo or buffalo on the menu.  Excellent cuisine matched by congenial ambiance. Guinness is on tap - and a fine selection of wines.  What more could you ask for?

title: Monument de la rafle du Vél’ d'Hiv’
Hotel Sophie Germain
description: The Sophie Germain hotel is ideally located on the left bank of Paris. Near Place Denfert- Rochereau, just a few minutes away from Montparnasse train station and the Latin Quarter. Very easy access to events and exhibitions organised at Porte de Versailles and Villepinte. The Sophie Germain hotel will be your starting point to discover the beauties of Paris.
